Back In Time

Copyright (C) 2008 Oprea Dan <dan@le-web.org>

1. About

	Back In Time is a simple backup tool for GNOME Desktop, inspired from "flyback project".
	You only need to specify 3 things:
		* where to save backups
		* what to backup
		* backup frequency (manual, every hour, every day, every month)

	Translations:
		* French (fr)
		* Spanish (es)

1.1. Credits

	* Francisco Manuel Garc√≠a Claramonte <franciscomanuel.garcia@hispalinux.es>: Spanish translations

2. INSTALL

2.1. Debian/Ubuntu

	Main application:

		./makedeb.sh
		sudo dpkg -i backintime-<version>.deb

	Translations:

		sudo dpkg -i backintime-<language>-<version>.deb

2.2. Other

	Main application:

		sudo ./install.sh

	Translations:

		./translate.sh
		sudo ./install_locale.sh <language>

